WEBVTT

00:24.162 --> 00:25.043
Good morning, Northridge.

00:25.063 --> 00:25.785
How are you guys?

00:27.988 --> 00:28.769
Good to see you.

00:29.911 --> 00:33.337
My name is Pete, one of the pastors here at Northridge, and we're just honored that you guys are here.

00:33.357 --> 00:35.099
We're gonna welcome those of you that are watching online.

00:35.119 --> 00:36.682
We're so glad you guys are with us.

00:36.742 --> 00:47.058
And I know that there were some problems getting in today, and some of you were stuck in traffic for a while, and I know that's such a pain, but isn't that such a cool problem to have when there's traffic coming to church?

00:47.138 --> 00:49.362
I love that.

00:51.042 --> 00:57.088
I love that because I was already here in the building and not sitting in it, but I still think it's kind of cool.

00:57.388 --> 01:02.614
And just always reminded of how amazing God is and the cool things he's doing.

01:02.654 --> 01:12.444
And I know a lot of people are talking about the million meals, and I can't tell you anything about it, but Pastor Brad's going to be here next week to talk to you all about the results of the million meals campaign that we've been up to.

01:12.484 --> 01:17.308
And thousands of you out there volunteering that have done such an amazing job with that.

01:17.368 --> 01:18.930
We're just so grateful for that.

01:19.362 --> 01:25.111
So we've been in this series called In With The New that we started all the way back the very first week of the year.

01:25.592 --> 01:33.704
And the series idea was this, that everybody goes into a new year and they want that new year to be better than the last year, right?

01:33.745 --> 01:40.475
We all had those hopes, dreams, wishes, desires going into this year that 2024 is gonna be better than 2023.

01:41.156 --> 01:47.506
But the reality is 2024 is gonna be a whole lot like 2023 for you.

01:47.714 --> 01:50.357
If there's not some things that you change up in your life, right?

01:50.418 --> 01:58.048
Just expecting that somehow life is gonna create all these different paths for you and all these things are gonna fall onto place is not realistic.

01:58.488 --> 02:02.373
So the reality is we've been looking at where are the things that we need to add?

02:02.393 --> 02:04.856
Where are the new things we need to implement into our life?

02:04.896 --> 02:10.103
And maybe what are some of the old things that we need to let go of in order to make this year different than the other years?

02:10.143 --> 02:15.250
To make this a year that we actually step into becoming who we were created to become?

02:15.938 --> 02:32.274
And one of the things that I know without a shadow of a doubt that every single person here is going to need at some point over the course of 2024, and a bunch of you have already needed this in the first two months, and that is courage, right?

02:32.314 --> 02:45.426
There's so many moments in our life that require courage, that require us to push through our fear and allow God to work in our life to leave that comfort zone and step into whatever it is he has for us.

02:45.730 --> 02:47.453
But it's easy to talk about courage.

02:47.473 --> 02:49.917
It's one thing to have to actually develop it.

02:50.638 --> 02:51.740
And I'm gonna look at a story today.

02:51.760 --> 02:55.766
I think there are obviously hundreds of stories in scripture about courage.

02:56.407 --> 03:01.074
I mean, there's hardly a chapter or a book that doesn't talk in some way about courage.

03:01.595 --> 03:13.554
But there's a moment in a main character's life, the main character being Moses, where we can really dissect like what's going on in his mind in that moment that is keeping him from developing courage.

03:13.730 --> 03:17.638
And by seeing that, I think what you're going to see is he's got two thoughts, right?

03:17.758 --> 03:19.722
And these two thoughts are kind of paralyzing him.

03:20.283 --> 03:29.522
And my guess is that there is a bunch of you who have these same two thoughts in this very moment that are keeping you from stepping into your moment.

03:29.986 --> 03:32.949
So let me set it up for you real quick and then we'll look at the passage, right?

03:33.089 --> 03:43.718
So Moses at this point in his life is about 80 years old, which is a fact that I think we need to point out because whenever we talk about courage, I think some people think that courage is like a young person's game, right?

03:44.018 --> 03:48.042
Like courage is something you need when you're taking risk when you're 20 or 30, right?

03:48.262 --> 03:55.188
But then as you get older, you just kind of put it on cruise control and you're just kind of gonna drift through life and you're not taking those risks anymore.

03:55.208 --> 03:57.029
You're not stepping out in faith anymore.

03:57.090 --> 03:58.371
You know, you kind of made it.

03:58.631 --> 03:59.972
You let the generations

03:59.952 --> 04:05.399
behind you do that, but what we see throughout scripture is God could care less about age.

04:05.419 --> 04:07.502
He could care less about your physical appearance.

04:07.662 --> 04:16.815
He could actually even care less about some of the gifts and the abilities that you have, even though he's the one that's given them to you, because there's a lot more about him and what he's doing in and through your life.

04:16.895 --> 04:18.677
So I don't want you to hit this news button.

04:19.018 --> 04:27.890
If you're in some of the later chapters of your life, I believe that in every chapter God is calling you to trust him, to step out in faith and to exhibit courage.

04:28.322 --> 04:29.543
So Moses is around 80.

04:29.704 --> 04:32.487
He's in the wilderness where he's been for four decades.

04:32.767 --> 04:36.731
The reason he's there is because he's kind of on the run or is hiding.

04:37.392 --> 04:50.267
So what had happened was Moses throughout his life got a front row seat to the injustices that had been pushed on his people, the Hebrews, the Israelites, God's people, right?

04:50.407 --> 04:51.348
By the Egyptians.

04:51.668 --> 04:52.930
He had seen this over and over.

04:53.590 --> 04:56.754
One day he sees an Egyptian mistreating a Hebrew.

04:57.378 --> 04:58.600
He steps into that moment.

04:59.341 --> 05:02.586
And in rage, he ends up killing the Egyptian.

05:03.207 --> 05:05.270
So that's like even back then, a no-no.

05:05.631 --> 05:07.614
And so he's afraid.

05:07.654 --> 05:08.315
He runs.

05:08.596 --> 05:09.177
He has shame.

05:09.197 --> 05:09.778
He has guilt.

05:09.958 --> 05:10.759
And he's hiding.

05:10.799 --> 05:15.046
And all of a sudden, one day, he's out just doing what it is he does.

05:15.106 --> 05:16.208
He's a shepherd, right?

05:16.228 --> 05:17.490
He's just monitoring his business.

05:17.830 --> 05:19.633
And he's walking through the wilderness.

05:19.934 --> 05:21.055
And there is a bush.

05:21.416 --> 05:22.738
And the bush is on fire.

05:23.426 --> 05:26.731
Now, if you grew up in church, you've heard the story a hundred times, right?

05:27.072 --> 05:29.776
The bush is on fire, but the bush is not burning up.

05:30.517 --> 05:34.884
And then there's a voice that comes out of the bush, and it's God, right?

05:34.964 --> 05:37.728
And I have no idea what God's voice sounds like.

05:38.088 --> 05:44.598
I just imagine that, like, if you audibly heard the voice of God, you would know in that moment that it's God, right?

05:44.739 --> 05:46.962
Like, you don't think it's your cousin.

05:47.042 --> 05:54.351
or a sibling that's like, whoa, that, yup, that's God for sure, because there's a bush and it's on fire, but it's not burning up.

05:54.432 --> 05:56.454
Like there's something that's going on here.

05:56.534 --> 05:58.397
This is not normal.

05:58.877 --> 06:05.526
And so God, out of nowhere, introduces himself to Moses through this bush that's on fire, but it's not burning up.

06:06.827 --> 06:15.058
And in this moment, God kind of interrupts Moses' pity party, and he doesn't interrupt and communicate

06:15.362 --> 06:17.584
to Moses, that he's a screw up.

06:18.145 --> 06:22.749
He doesn't remind him of his past, doesn't remind him of his inadequacies, none of that.

06:23.170 --> 06:27.274
In this moment, God introduces himself and he says, Moses, I have a challenge for you.

06:27.814 --> 06:30.697
I have a calling on your life that I want you to step into.

06:30.717 --> 06:43.890
And I want you to do the most important task of going to the Hebrews, announcing to them that I'm sending you, that I'm setting them free, and I want you to go and confront Pharaoh, the most powerful man in the region, and demand that he let my people go.

06:44.418 --> 06:53.592
And that's where we picked this story up with Moses' response right after God who's speaking to him through a bush that's on fire that's not burning up.

06:54.553 --> 06:56.616
This was his response to God.

06:57.157 --> 07:00.302
Moses answered, what if they do not believe me?

07:00.943 --> 07:05.850
Or they don't listen to me and they say, the Lord did not appear to you.

07:05.910 --> 07:09.035
Then the Lord said to him, what is that in your hand?

07:09.556 --> 07:10.898
A staff, he replied.

07:11.458 --> 07:12.760
The Lord said, throw it on the ground.

07:12.800 --> 07:13.842
Let's just do it on the ground.

07:14.102 --> 07:14.984
And it became a snake.

07:15.465 --> 07:18.390
And he ran from it, which I just think that's funny.

07:18.410 --> 07:20.734
Like I'd like to see that whole saint.

07:20.754 --> 07:25.401
Like there's a bush that's on fire and God is talking to you, but you ran from the snake.

07:25.422 --> 07:25.922
Okay.

07:25.942 --> 07:29.989
So then the Lord said to him, reach out your hand and take it by the tail.

07:31.071 --> 07:32.033
That's when I'd be out.

07:32.193 --> 07:35.218
I'd be, I don't care if it's a bush that's on fire that's not burning up.

07:35.426 --> 07:37.069
I'm not picking up a snake by the tail.

07:37.109 --> 07:37.650
I'm not doing it.

07:37.690 --> 07:43.539
But Moses reaches out and it took hold of the snake and it turned back into a staff in his hand.

07:44.220 --> 07:52.734
This said the Lord is so that they may believe that the Lord, the God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob has appeared to you.

07:53.455 --> 07:54.838
So that's the scene, right?

07:54.918 --> 07:55.799
That's what's going on.

07:56.120 --> 07:59.986
And what you're going to see in Moses's life is a couple thoughts that he has.

08:00.162 --> 08:03.848
Now, there's a lot to unpack there, but I want to point out these two thoughts.

08:03.928 --> 08:07.914
And the reason this is important, again, is because some of you have the exact same two thoughts.

08:08.555 --> 08:13.583
And the reason these thoughts are important is because thoughts are things, right?

08:13.723 --> 08:14.825
Thoughts matter.

08:14.885 --> 08:22.678
The thoughts that you allow yourself to entertain, and we talk about this sometime, but the Bible talks about in Proverbs that as a man thinks so he is.

08:22.758 --> 08:27.986
In other words, your life is moving in the direction of your most powerful thoughts.

08:28.418 --> 08:37.309
So the thoughts that we allow our mind to dwell on and think about and repeat over and over are impacting the direction that your life is going.

08:37.770 --> 08:42.175
So I want to look at these two thoughts that Moses had, and you just kind of like hanging there with me.

08:42.236 --> 08:52.268
Let me know if this identifies with you in any way, if any of this sounds familiar, but the two thoughts that Moses is having that are robbing him of courage, the first one is this.

08:52.669 --> 08:53.650
What if something goes wrong?

08:54.402 --> 08:55.543
Right, what if something goes wrong?

08:55.783 --> 09:11.739
And it's easy to identify this thought in Moses because the very first thing that he says back to God, when God gives him this moment, this calling that he needs to step into, his very first response, the very first two words that come out of his mouth are, what if?

09:13.261 --> 09:15.303
What if they don't believe me?

09:16.264 --> 09:21.289
What if they think that I didn't actually have a conversation with you in a burning bush, right?

09:21.369 --> 09:22.450
Well, you know,

09:22.626 --> 09:24.729
Honestly, it's kind of a valid what if, right?

09:24.969 --> 09:26.892
But he starts off with what if.

09:27.413 --> 09:35.965
What if should always be an indicator to you that there's a level of fear, and I call it like the initial level of fear.

09:36.025 --> 09:39.570
This is where fear usually first shows up in our life.

09:40.050 --> 09:42.674
It's a fear about something out here.

09:43.362 --> 09:45.685
It's a fear about the circumstances.

09:45.745 --> 09:55.619
It's a fear of, if I step into this moment, if I do this, if I take this job, if I go into this marriage, if we have kids, blah, blah, blah, blah, right?

09:56.200 --> 10:00.165
If I step into this, something out here is gonna go wrong.

10:00.666 --> 10:07.014
The circumstances, the events, whatever, are not gonna work out the way that I think they're going to work out.

10:07.455 --> 10:12.722
This is the level of fear where it initially takes hold of us, and you can get trapped.

10:12.834 --> 10:14.196
right in that what if loop.

10:14.556 --> 10:15.938
I get trapped in it all the time.

10:16.078 --> 10:18.782
I can be a champion whatever, right?

10:18.842 --> 10:26.511
I can spin off all kinds of like crazy what ifs that not only scare me but scare the people around me because they're like I didn't even think about that possibility, right?

10:26.812 --> 10:32.299
Like I'm really good at finding worst case scenarios in certain situations and some of you are too.

10:33.180 --> 10:37.906
Some of you right now you're spinning off of what if I can't lose weight and what if I never get married and

10:38.338 --> 10:39.901
What if I get married and I can't have kids?

10:40.322 --> 10:43.848
And what if I get married and I'm not good at like the whole marriage thing, all right?

10:43.868 --> 10:46.252
Or what if I have kids and I'm not good at being a parent?

10:46.272 --> 10:49.558
And what if I go to that job interview and they say no, right?

10:49.598 --> 10:53.645
And what if I can't save enough money to send my kids to college one day?

10:53.685 --> 10:57.752
And what if, you know, my boss, has this ever happened to you guys?

10:57.773 --> 11:03.122
You get like a text from your boss or your manager and all it says is, hey, could we meet tomorrow at 10 a.m.?

11:05.602 --> 11:06.703
And that's all you need, right?

11:06.724 --> 11:09.567
You are off to the races with the what-ifs, right?

11:09.607 --> 11:10.749
What if I did something wrong?

11:10.769 --> 11:11.910
What if they're gonna fire me?

11:11.991 --> 11:18.599
What if, you know, like it just starts, and what's worse is when you say like, okay, yeah, what is this about?

11:18.700 --> 11:26.911
And then you see those three little bubbles, like underneath that, like they're thinking, and then the bubbles disappear, and they don't say anything.

11:27.231 --> 11:27.952
Like that's the word.

11:27.992 --> 11:31.176
Like now you're, again, you're the champion whatever, right?

11:31.296 --> 11:33.439
Of all the things that could go wrong.

11:34.200 --> 11:35.442
Here's the flip to what-if.

11:35.778 --> 11:42.589
And this is a fun little trick that my wife and I kind of play on each other when one of the two of us gets stuck in that what-if loop.

11:42.929 --> 11:43.891
This week it was her.

11:43.951 --> 11:50.841
So a couple years ago when we had our daughter, she decided to kind of leave her corporate job and stay at home with her daughter.

11:50.861 --> 11:57.472
And now she's, you know, she still wants to stay at home with her daughter, but she's at a place now where she's like, I want to kind of start this new business.

11:57.492 --> 11:59.916
I want to go back in the corporate world, but I want to kind of do my own thing.

12:00.316 --> 12:03.020
And so she's been working on that and creating her website and all that.

12:03.040 --> 12:04.082
But this week,

12:04.162 --> 12:05.785
She's been stuck in the what ifs, right?

12:06.085 --> 12:17.765
What if I don't get any clients and what if I can't do a good job for my clients and what if, like what if, and the little flip, the little trick is we'll look each other in our eyes and this case, this week, it was me saying it to her.

12:17.785 --> 12:23.053
It's like, hey, what if it all works out, right?

12:23.073 --> 12:23.855
That's the flip, right?

12:23.955 --> 12:28.803
What if it all works out because the vast majority of time in our lives, guess what?

12:29.344 --> 12:30.706
It's all worked out.

12:31.426 --> 12:31.686
Right?

12:31.726 --> 12:34.070
So what if for you it all works out?

12:34.650 --> 12:36.713
Because the vast majority of time it has.

12:37.174 --> 12:39.297
What if it all works out?

12:39.317 --> 12:41.159
What if you do lose the weight?

12:41.439 --> 12:42.982
What if you are able to have kids?

12:43.422 --> 12:43.602
Right?

12:43.823 --> 12:45.104
What if you do get the job?

12:45.385 --> 12:49.651
What if you step into that new opportunity and it's even better than you imagined?

12:50.652 --> 12:52.574
Because so many times in your life it has.

12:53.736 --> 12:54.697
So what if it all works out?

12:56.660 --> 12:58.162
Will it all work out for you?

12:58.530 --> 13:00.275
No, it's not.

13:00.375 --> 13:01.879
No, it's not all going to work out for you.

13:01.939 --> 13:03.182
And that's OK, right?

13:03.222 --> 13:05.268
Because you are not going to be any worse off.

13:05.368 --> 13:12.146
Because spinning off worst-case scenarios has never actually protected you from your worst fears.

13:12.610 --> 13:14.172
Not a single time.

13:14.253 --> 13:14.854
It's a lie.

13:15.034 --> 13:15.835
It's a deception.

13:16.095 --> 13:17.858
You think you're somehow protecting yourself.

13:17.918 --> 13:21.504
That's what your mind's trying to do when it's spinning off all these what-ifs.

13:21.524 --> 13:22.746
Your mind's saying, hey, be careful.

13:22.806 --> 13:23.487
This could happen.

13:23.507 --> 13:24.068
That could happen.

13:24.108 --> 13:25.911
I don't want you to embarrass yourself.

13:26.191 --> 13:27.453
I don't want you to have to go through pain.

13:27.473 --> 13:29.136
I don't want you to have to go through rejection.

13:29.797 --> 13:35.506
It's trying to protect you, but it's playing a trick on you because it never works out that way.

13:35.874 --> 13:43.562
you're just introducing yourself to becoming a slave of the mental torture over something that probably will never come to fruition.

13:44.483 --> 13:51.171
Now, what I think is interesting, you got to look real carefully in this text, but there's a clue here from Moses and his fear.

13:51.971 --> 13:56.076
And if you notice his initial fear when he says, what if they don't believe me?

13:56.356 --> 14:01.682
Notice he's not doubting God, at least not directly.

14:01.826 --> 14:05.551
I think he kind of knows better in this moment than to do that, right?

14:06.052 --> 14:09.217
He's not saying, you know, God, what if you can't do this?

14:09.898 --> 14:13.803
And what if you don't have enough plagues to change the Egyptians' minds?

14:13.823 --> 14:15.105
And what if you run out of strength?

14:15.366 --> 14:16.687
Or God, what if you run out of miracles?

14:16.768 --> 14:19.031
No, his fear's directed in another direction.

14:19.612 --> 14:23.037
And if you see it, he says, what if they don't believe me?

14:23.057 --> 14:23.778
Now, who's the they?

14:23.818 --> 14:26.922
In this case, it's his own people.

14:27.663 --> 14:28.364
It's the Hebrews.

14:28.464 --> 14:29.586
It's the Israelites.

14:30.082 --> 14:31.924
Right, that's who he's afraid of.

14:32.264 --> 14:34.026
He's afraid of how they're gonna react.

14:34.747 --> 14:35.587
Who's he doubting?

14:35.948 --> 14:36.668
The Hebrews.

14:37.609 --> 14:38.830
But who is he supposed to help?

14:40.032 --> 14:40.672
The Hebrews.

14:41.173 --> 14:44.136
Who is it that he's absolutely passionate about protecting?

14:44.636 --> 14:45.257
The Hebrews.

14:45.957 --> 14:47.539
And so this is a really interesting thing.

14:47.579 --> 14:48.700
You gotta pay attention to this.

14:49.501 --> 14:55.387
The thing that you're afraid of is often a clue to the thing that you're assigned to.

14:56.948 --> 14:58.930
The thing that you're afraid of

14:59.394 --> 15:03.620
is often the clue to the thing that you're actually assigned to.

15:03.640 --> 15:07.686
In other words, fear is often a mask for passion.

15:08.848 --> 15:18.963
So anytime somebody's talking to me about their fears, I'm so afraid of this and what if this happens, what if that happens, I start listening real intently because I know underneath all that fear, there's actually passion.

15:19.544 --> 15:29.298
There's some kind of calling, there's some kind of like moment of courage that they need because they're talking about something that deeply matters to them.

15:29.890 --> 15:37.941
Fear is most often going to arise around the things that you're called to, the things that matter to you, the things that you're passionate about.

15:39.162 --> 15:40.604
And I see this in my own life.

15:41.425 --> 15:48.755
If I follow my fear, the reality is my fear is almost like a compass, right, to what it is I'm passionate about.

15:49.556 --> 15:54.002
So I'll give you an example from my own life that a lot of you would never be aware of.

15:54.562 --> 15:57.066
So I don't take myself very seriously.

15:57.086 --> 15:58.728
You guys have probably figured that out by now.

15:59.129 --> 16:01.392
But I do take my calling very serious.

16:01.773 --> 16:06.840
And I take this moment and what I get to do in this moment extremely serious.

16:06.860 --> 16:10.846
I spend a lot of time praying and preparing for a lot of different reasons.

16:10.866 --> 16:18.898
But for one reason, I'm like, people come to church and they're like giving of their most important resource time to be here.

16:18.978 --> 16:24.645
to worship together, to hear God's word, to be challenged, to become more like Jesus.

16:24.665 --> 16:27.890
And I take that so serious, right?

16:27.930 --> 16:35.960
But because I'm passionate about it, because there's a calling there, there's also a tremendous amount of fear that happens in my life.

16:35.980 --> 16:38.563
Do you know when the last time is I felt extremely fearful?

16:39.845 --> 16:42.629
It was 10 minutes ago, and I'll show you exactly where I was.

16:43.329 --> 16:46.834
There's this room back here, they call it backstage.

16:47.202 --> 16:50.365
And if you, I don't know if you've ever been back there, I'm gonna take you back there right now.

16:50.426 --> 16:51.066
Go back here.

16:51.106 --> 16:52.428
There's people back here.

16:52.468 --> 16:55.051
Are y'all playing cards or what?

16:55.071 --> 16:56.532
No, okay.

16:56.552 --> 17:03.320
So this is backstage and this is where I stand before they push me out there, right?

17:03.820 --> 17:09.627
And when I'm standing here, first of all, I wait until the last possible second to walk back here.

17:09.687 --> 17:11.669
Like usually people are panicked like, where is he?

17:12.009 --> 17:16.434
Well, I'm gonna wait until that last minute, until they drag me back here to stand here,

17:16.546 --> 17:23.054
Because in this moment, I feel a tremendous amount of fear, like borderline panic attacks.

17:23.414 --> 17:39.474
I was trying earlier to explain to somebody what it feels like when I'm back here, but it feels like I'm in a car at a red light, and I have the gas pedal pressed all the way down, and at the same time I have the brake pedal also pressed all the way down.

17:39.746 --> 17:39.986
Right?

17:40.007 --> 17:44.495
So it's this anxiousness like I'm ready to go, but then it breaks all the way down because I don't want to go.

17:44.536 --> 17:46.820
That's the feeling that kind of comes up inside of me.

17:47.321 --> 17:54.235
And in those two minutes standing back here, oh my gosh, the what ifs, like they start pretty simple like, well, what if my zipper's down?

17:54.555 --> 17:55.858
Or what if my...

17:55.970 --> 17:57.592
You know, my shoe's untied.

17:58.032 --> 18:06.300
Or what if I go out there and completely forget what I'm talking about, which is possible, Pete, because you lost your car keys three times this morning before you left.

18:06.360 --> 18:07.781
Like, you could do that, right?

18:08.042 --> 18:12.966
What if you go out there and you say something stupid and go off script and you get canceled?

18:13.307 --> 18:14.868
Like, what if that happens?

18:14.968 --> 18:19.953
Or what if you go out there and it just doesn't connect and they don't get it or they don't understand it?

18:20.073 --> 18:22.115
And you know, what if all that work is for nothing?

18:22.135 --> 18:23.597
What if you screw this up?

18:24.157 --> 18:25.138
All these what ifs.

18:25.538 --> 18:27.340
It's paralyzing to me.

18:28.121 --> 18:29.363
And then something happens.

18:30.004 --> 18:39.076
Back here, they open up this curtain and I walk out here and I still feel like in this moment when I'm walking out, I still feel pretty anxious.

18:39.136 --> 18:41.198
Like, is there somebody else that could do this?

18:41.299 --> 18:42.841
Like, I'll give you my notes.

18:43.682 --> 18:45.164
I'm sure you can nail this, right?

18:45.484 --> 18:47.026
But it's panicked, but it's like two likes.

18:47.086 --> 18:47.827
I'm out here, right?

18:47.847 --> 18:48.868
So I just keep walking.

18:49.289 --> 18:53.234
And the moment that I get right here, and this has happened for me hundreds of times,

18:54.114 --> 19:03.652
When moment I step from what if into what is, in that moment, all the fear and anxiety just disappear like that.

19:04.754 --> 19:07.079
Every single time, right?

19:09.463 --> 19:15.735
But what has to happen is I have to work through those what ifs.

19:15.755 --> 19:17.298
I have to push past that.

19:17.762 --> 19:18.062
Right?

19:18.343 --> 19:21.568
And knowing that any one of those scenarios actually is possible.

19:21.888 --> 19:22.029
Right?

19:22.049 --> 19:27.958
But I have to push through the what ifs and step into what is for all that to disappear.

19:28.478 --> 19:28.679
Right?

19:28.959 --> 19:29.981
To be used by God.

19:30.321 --> 19:35.429
To allow His strength to support where I might be weak.

19:36.030 --> 19:39.355
I have to go through the what ifs to get to the what is.

19:40.557 --> 19:40.737
Right?

19:40.858 --> 19:46.386
And the reason that this is important is because I want you to understand that the fears that you have right now in your life

19:46.722 --> 19:49.326
None of your fears are actually in this present moment.

19:50.528 --> 19:51.749
None of them.

19:51.769 --> 19:54.894
All the fears that you have are fears about the future.

19:55.395 --> 20:01.163
What you think could happen in five minutes or in five days or in five years.

20:01.243 --> 20:02.185
That's where the fear is.

20:02.505 --> 20:04.048
It's not in the present.

20:04.068 --> 20:10.918
And so you have Moses that's standing here in front of a burning bush that's not burning up, right?

20:11.338 --> 20:13.682
Like the God of the universe is talking to him.

20:13.702 --> 20:16.466
I've got to think this is a really special moment for him.

20:16.834 --> 20:17.094
Right?

20:17.615 --> 20:25.284
Of all moments in your life, to want to be fully present, I would think it would be the moment the God, the God of the universe is talking to you through a burning bush.

20:25.584 --> 20:26.966
But is Moses really present?

20:27.246 --> 20:27.447
No.

20:27.807 --> 20:29.809
And we see that from his very first statement.

20:29.889 --> 20:35.656
He says, what if they, and instantly he leaves what is and he goes to what if.

20:36.758 --> 20:40.562
And I'm telling you, the land of what if will eat you alive.

20:40.642 --> 20:42.645
He misses staying in the moment with what is.

20:43.346 --> 20:53.021
But God in his graciousness, if you notice God's response, God's moving him, transitioning him from what if back to what is.

20:53.301 --> 20:56.947
You might have missed it, but we just read that in those two verses, right?

20:56.967 --> 20:57.447
We read this.

20:57.828 --> 21:00.372
Moses' answer was, what is it?

21:00.712 --> 21:01.554
What if, right?

21:02.014 --> 21:07.122
God in the very next verse, when he responds to him, starts with what is?

21:08.002 --> 21:11.587
He's shifting him from the what-ifs to what-is.

21:11.727 --> 21:14.191
And he says, Moses, what's in your hand?

21:15.172 --> 21:19.017
So in that moment, boom, Moses is right back into the present.

21:19.218 --> 21:20.559
Oh, I'm holding the staff.

21:21.541 --> 21:22.222
I'm holding the staff.

21:22.262 --> 21:23.503
Like, this is what I do now, God.

21:23.544 --> 21:24.104
I'm a shepherd.

21:24.144 --> 21:25.446
Like, it's not impressive.

21:25.466 --> 21:26.428
No, he's impressed by it.

21:26.488 --> 21:33.958
I walk around with the staff and I twirl it and hit sheep with it or whatever you do with the staff when you're a shepherd, right?

21:34.218 --> 21:36.882
Like, this is just, it's pretty common.

21:37.026 --> 21:38.648
ordinary and God's like, oh, really?

21:38.688 --> 21:39.950
It's common and ordinary?

21:40.270 --> 21:41.893
Take that staff and throw it on the ground.

21:42.654 --> 21:46.479
And Moses takes the staff and he throws it on the ground, and that's when it turns into a snake, right?

21:46.839 --> 21:48.862
And it's if God is saying, let me show you.

21:49.362 --> 21:56.973
Let me just show you, Moses, the kind of extraordinary things I can do with something that may seem ordinary and unimpressive to you.

21:57.994 --> 22:00.978
God wants Moses to know that in that moment,

22:01.410 --> 22:07.060
He has in his hands everything that he needs for what God is gonna lead him to in the future.

22:08.182 --> 22:12.750
And part of the reason I think you're here today, and it's not by accident, by the way, right?

22:12.770 --> 22:18.059
You could be in a lot of different places right now, but you're sitting right here, you're watching this online right now in this moment.

22:18.420 --> 22:26.514
Part of what I think God's trying to say to you is, hey, what you have in your hand, your connections, your resources, as little as you might think they are,

22:26.754 --> 22:31.540
Your gifts, your abilities, your intellect, all the things he's placed into your life, your family, all of it.

22:32.641 --> 22:37.046
Everything you have today is enough for what I'm going to call you to do in the future.

22:37.867 --> 22:38.668
You just got to trust me.

22:40.230 --> 22:43.174
You just got to trust me.

22:43.214 --> 22:45.397
Got much Moses to know, and he wants all of us to know.

22:45.437 --> 22:47.860
You've got everything that you need.

22:48.460 --> 22:54.608
And if you think about Moses' story, that moment was such a cool moment.

22:54.688 --> 22:55.789
What is that in your hand?

22:55.909 --> 22:56.530
It's a staff.

22:57.026 --> 22:59.809
But what is it that God uses throughout Moses' life?

23:00.249 --> 23:04.013
What was it that God used to bring about the plagues that would change Pharaoh's mind?

23:04.453 --> 23:05.514
It was Moses' staff.

23:05.855 --> 23:10.559
What is it that God used when they came to the Red Sea and it looked like the enemy was closing in behind them?

23:10.579 --> 23:12.241
What is it that God used to part the Red Sea?

23:12.742 --> 23:13.622
Moses' staff.

23:14.283 --> 23:21.250
When Israelites were thirsty and I thought they were gonna die of thirst, what is it that God used to bring water out of a rock?

23:21.810 --> 23:23.072
It was Moses' staff.

23:23.672 --> 23:25.394
Moses, you got everything you need.

23:25.954 --> 23:36.144
For everything I'm gonna call you to in the future, and I will take what looks common, and what looks normal, and what looks unimpressive, and I'm gonna do extraordinary things to you, but you gotta trust me.

23:37.485 --> 23:46.734
Now, part of Moses's problem in this moment, and part of the problem that some of you are facing right now, whatever intersection you're at, is you're confusing courage and confidence.

23:47.675 --> 23:51.739
Moses has no confidence at this stage of his life, and that's no surprise, right?

23:51.839 --> 23:55.282
Given the current set of events that have happened up to this point,

23:55.394 --> 23:56.535
He has no confidence.

23:56.955 --> 24:00.659
So because he has no confidence, he doesn't think he can step into that moment of courage.

24:01.179 --> 24:07.786
Some of you have been waiting around for a long time to feel confident before you step into your moment.

24:08.286 --> 24:12.891
But you have to understand confidence is not a prerequisite, right?

24:13.131 --> 24:17.115
In fact, confidence is something that comes on the back end, right?

24:17.175 --> 24:24.882
To go back to my little illustration of standing backstage, I never feel confident when that curtain opens, not at all.

24:25.250 --> 24:27.293
I don't need confidence in that moment.

24:27.313 --> 24:29.836
Confidence may come later, may come after the fact.

24:30.277 --> 24:35.404
If I step in with courage and allow God to use me, there might be a little bit of confidence on the other side of it, maybe.

24:36.004 --> 24:37.747
But confidence is not a prerequisite.

24:37.767 --> 24:39.329
You don't wait until you feel confident.

24:39.449 --> 24:41.091
If you feel confident, you wouldn't need the courage.

24:42.193 --> 24:46.539
You act on the courage and you allow the confidence to come on the back end.

24:47.139 --> 24:50.864
But Moses, like a lot of you right now, he's still not convinced.

24:51.505 --> 24:52.947
So he keeps going.

24:52.987 --> 24:55.090
So he says this back to God.

24:55.490 --> 24:56.652
Pardon your servant, Lord.

24:56.672 --> 25:01.938
I have never been eloquent, neither in the past nor since you've spoken to your servant.

25:01.959 --> 25:03.861
I am slow of speech and tongue.

25:04.221 --> 25:06.965
And the Lord said to him, who gave human beings their mouths?

25:06.985 --> 25:08.227
Who makes them deferemute?

25:08.467 --> 25:10.310
Who gives them sight or makes them blind?

25:10.730 --> 25:12.452
Is it not I, the Lord?

25:12.492 --> 25:13.474
Now go.

25:13.494 --> 25:16.778
I will help you speak and I will teach you what to say.

25:17.799 --> 25:22.866
I love this interaction because God's so cool like this.

25:23.842 --> 25:28.226
It's more about what he doesn't say here than what he does say, right?

25:28.246 --> 25:29.367
Because what does he not say?

25:29.668 --> 25:32.310
He's not like, oh, Moses, no, dude, you're good.

25:32.531 --> 25:33.111
You're good.

25:33.191 --> 25:34.012
You're good at talking.

25:34.473 --> 25:35.253
Like, you're great.

25:35.273 --> 25:36.795
You're a great communicator, buddy.

25:36.835 --> 25:37.636
Just step out there.

25:38.056 --> 25:39.317
Like, you got this, you know?

25:39.357 --> 25:40.559
Like, he doesn't say that, right?

25:40.879 --> 25:42.981
He never is like, oh, you totally got to it.

25:43.001 --> 25:44.222
He's like, what's he say?

25:44.242 --> 25:48.567
He says, hey, who gave you the gifts and the abilities that you have?

25:48.627 --> 25:49.287
Was it not I?

25:50.208 --> 25:50.689
I'm with you.

25:51.409 --> 25:52.050
I'll help you.

25:52.546 --> 26:05.545
All right, you think that your gifts and your abilities in the stage that are at right now is as far as it's gonna go, do you not believe that I can step into your life at any moment and exponentially increase those gifts and those abilities that I originally gave you?

26:05.605 --> 26:10.312
See, here's the second thought that Moses has and this is the thought that some of you are having right now.

26:10.352 --> 26:13.297
And the second thought was, I'm just not qualified.

26:14.278 --> 26:15.119
I'm not qualified.

26:16.341 --> 26:19.566
Now, this is a deeper level of fear, right?

26:19.826 --> 26:22.450
Level one fear is fear about this out here.

26:22.530 --> 26:24.853
Something circumstantially could go wrong.

26:25.233 --> 26:31.241
Level two fear is a deeper, darker fear because the fear is not about what might happen out there.

26:31.301 --> 26:33.984
The fear is internal and it's about who you are.

26:34.825 --> 26:36.467
It's a fear about you're not qualified.

26:36.968 --> 26:40.372
It's a fear about you've got too much junk in your past that you can't get over.

26:40.412 --> 26:41.814
Nobody else will let you get over it.

26:42.174 --> 26:46.039
It's a fear about your gifts and your abilities and your inadequacies and your weaknesses.

26:46.339 --> 26:50.244
And it's a much deeper level of fear because it's not just something might go wrong.

26:50.485 --> 26:51.666
It's I think I'm wrong.

26:52.610 --> 26:53.692
I'm not the right person.

26:54.313 --> 26:56.155
I can't do this, right?

26:56.256 --> 26:56.696
Who am I?

26:56.716 --> 26:57.718
Have you ever felt that?

26:58.819 --> 26:59.581
I'm sure you have.

26:59.781 --> 27:01.744
I've felt it so many times in my life.

27:02.485 --> 27:03.907
It's like I've got too many weaknesses.

27:04.027 --> 27:06.031
I've got too much stuff in my past.

27:06.091 --> 27:07.873
I'm not good enough, right?

27:07.913 --> 27:09.776
That's everything that's going on for Moses.

27:10.958 --> 27:12.040
But how does God respond?

27:13.121 --> 27:14.403
Again, it responds with the question.

27:14.463 --> 27:19.411
It says, who gives human beings their mouths or their speech or their sight?

27:19.731 --> 27:20.493
Is it not I?

27:20.593 --> 27:21.394
In other words,

27:21.506 --> 27:24.209
Who makes people who they are?

27:25.210 --> 27:28.994
Who's in charge of everything that they have, right?

27:29.195 --> 27:31.597
Who's strength really matters in this moment?

27:31.858 --> 27:33.760
Is it your strength or is it my strength?

27:34.801 --> 27:40.407
So with the original fear, God comes to Moses and says, I'm going to shift you from what if to what is?

27:40.467 --> 27:43.170
And that's going to be a powerful transition and moment for you.

27:43.831 --> 27:49.938
And in that second level of fear, he says, I'm going to shift you from thinking about who you're not to reflecting on who I am.

27:50.626 --> 27:56.134
Because as you move forward, encourage in this moment, it's actually not about your strengths and abilities, although I've given you those things.

27:56.474 --> 27:59.599
It's about what I'm going to do through those strengths and abilities.

27:59.639 --> 28:03.184
It's about the fact that you're not going alone, because I'm going to be with you.

28:03.204 --> 28:18.706
And I think one of the reasons that you and I struggle so much with fear throughout our life, because we believe in some way that the quality of our future is directly tied to the quality of our gifts and our abilities and our discernment

28:19.266 --> 28:19.526
Right?

28:20.127 --> 28:21.129
We think it's about us.

28:22.251 --> 28:25.276
But God has never been impressed with human strength.

28:25.856 --> 28:29.843
God's never been impressed with our gifts and our abilities even though he's the one that gave him to us.

28:30.544 --> 28:30.784
Right?

28:30.804 --> 28:37.875
This is a God who again and again shows up and he shines brightest where it's needed the most.

28:39.298 --> 28:41.101
But Moses just can't see it in this moment.

28:41.742 --> 28:44.947
He's stuck and it's one excuse after another.

28:45.007 --> 28:47.090
Moses looks at his past

28:47.714 --> 28:57.245
Right, Moses is looking at all of his weaknesses, all of his limitations, and he sees this path, like it's clear, God's made the path clear.

28:57.625 --> 29:01.329
This is what I want you to do, Moses, walk this path, I'm gonna use you in a mighty way.

29:01.690 --> 29:11.160
But he sees his past and his weaknesses and all this stuff, almost like this giant boulder that's standing in the way, that's keeping him from moving forward.

29:11.240 --> 29:12.782
That's how he views all these things.

29:13.923 --> 29:16.466
One of my favorite quotes is from a Roman emperor,

29:16.962 --> 29:21.708
Marcus Aurelius, and he says this, what stands in the way becomes the way.

29:22.890 --> 29:24.072
I've always loved that quote.

29:24.092 --> 29:27.436
What stands in a way becomes the way.

29:27.476 --> 29:39.512
In other words, that thing that you think is holding you back, that thing that you think is blocking you from living out whatever life it is that God has for you, your past, your weaknesses, your limitations, all that stuff.

29:39.552 --> 29:44.279
Like what if, right, the obstacle was the way?

29:45.440 --> 29:46.642
What if it's not a setback?

29:47.426 --> 29:49.649
What if it's a set up, right?

29:49.669 --> 29:54.234
What if Moses could have just seen everything that had happened up in his past up to that moment?

29:55.155 --> 30:00.602
And his lack of strength, his lack of gifts, his lack of abilities, all of that.

30:00.622 --> 30:01.803
That wasn't a setback.

30:01.923 --> 30:02.784
That's how he viewed it.

30:03.045 --> 30:03.846
It wasn't a setback.

30:04.026 --> 30:05.067
It was a set up.

30:05.468 --> 30:09.513
He was perfectly positioned to be used by God.

30:10.954 --> 30:14.098
But it takes a tremendous amount of courage

30:15.714 --> 30:19.399
to look at what's standing in your way as the way.

30:21.322 --> 30:21.982
But I bet it is.

30:22.703 --> 30:37.463
I bet it is because unless we're exposed to difficulties and stresses and adversity and situations that we never want to be in, we cannot become fully the person that we're capable of becoming.

30:38.485 --> 30:39.266
We need those.

30:40.027 --> 30:45.394
And as much as I don't like to admit that I feel like I'm having a panic attack,

30:45.506 --> 30:48.709
for two minutes when I'm standing backstage, I actually need that.

30:49.630 --> 30:57.779
I need that because what happens is I get broken to a place where I am like putty in God's hands, right?

30:58.100 --> 30:58.861
I am desperate.

30:59.181 --> 31:03.045
I need him in that moment and it's part of that process, right?

31:03.085 --> 31:05.808
What if the obstacle was the way?

31:07.350 --> 31:14.898
One of the most common questions that people ask me and they ask it in lots of different ways, but they'll ask, when do I know that I'm ready?

31:15.938 --> 31:20.845
Like when do I know that I'm ready to trust God and step into that moment?

31:21.225 --> 31:25.411
Like when do I know I'm ready to leave my comfort zone?

31:26.492 --> 31:32.541
And the truth about me and the truth about you is that we're actually never gonna feel ready.

31:33.742 --> 31:38.248
You're never gonna be ready for the most important and the most challenging moments of your life.

31:38.829 --> 31:39.750
You're never gonna feel ready.

31:40.632 --> 31:43.656
The good news is God loves using people who aren't ready.

31:44.737 --> 31:45.298
He loves it.

31:45.698 --> 31:47.020
That's really all they has to work with.

31:48.242 --> 31:49.003
Think about the Bible.

31:49.023 --> 31:55.452
Think about all the stories you've grown up learning in the Bible, or maybe it's kind of new to you, and you're just picking it up and kind of reading through some of these stories.

31:55.812 --> 32:07.128
Like, is there ever a single moment anywhere in the Bible where God comes to somebody with a difficult task, a calling, a moment that they need to step into, and you're like, ooh, pick me.

32:07.288 --> 32:07.829
I got this.

32:08.790 --> 32:09.191
I'm ready.

32:09.251 --> 32:09.832
I'm prayed up.

32:09.992 --> 32:11.554
I've got all the gifts and abilities.

32:11.614 --> 32:12.696
Let's go.

32:12.736 --> 32:14.258
No.

32:14.594 --> 32:15.595
It never happens.

32:16.036 --> 32:21.423
Everybody kind of reluctantly steps into that moment and they don't feel like they're ready.

32:21.464 --> 32:23.306
They don't feel like they're adequate.

32:24.047 --> 32:29.675
And so if you want to make an impact, big or small in your life, you've got to get comfortable with being uncomfortable.

32:30.736 --> 32:37.285
Almost all the growth in your life is going to happen on the other side of your comfort zone.

32:38.167 --> 32:43.474
There's something I've heard pretty much my whole life in church and it's

32:43.746 --> 32:45.208
I love Christians.

32:45.268 --> 32:46.049
I really am one.

32:48.011 --> 32:48.892
Good to know.

32:49.413 --> 32:50.034
I love Christians.

32:50.294 --> 32:52.917
But as Christians, sometimes we say some stupid things, right?

32:53.418 --> 33:02.769
And one of the things that I heard growing up in church my whole life was fear and faith cannot coexist.

33:03.730 --> 33:05.492
I've seen it on t-shirts before, right?

33:05.592 --> 33:07.555
Fear and faith cannot coexist.

33:08.336 --> 33:09.237
That is so stupid.

33:09.998 --> 33:10.598
It really is.

33:10.658 --> 33:13.682
Fear and faith can absolutely

33:13.794 --> 33:20.421
In fact, like they're like these tight-knit cousins inside of my soul, right?

33:20.501 --> 33:28.669
Like fear and faith have always coexisted in my life and more than likely fear and faith have always coexisted in your life, right?

33:29.169 --> 33:32.793
In fact, if you don't have fear, why would you even need faith?

33:33.774 --> 33:39.579
And it's when the fear rises up in your life, that's the moment in which you need faith.

33:39.599 --> 33:42.162
And that's the moment in which the faith kicks in.

33:42.594 --> 33:47.340
And so it's not so much that it's an absence of fear, it's the presence of trust.

33:48.261 --> 33:52.686
In other words, faith doesn't eliminate fear, it overrides it.

33:54.148 --> 34:00.316
So if I go back to my silly little illustration when I'm standing back there, I actually never lose the fear.

34:01.818 --> 34:05.662
It's just my faith in that moment overrides the fear.

34:06.884 --> 34:11.890
And so part of what I wanna help you understand is that inside of every single one of you in this moment,

34:12.098 --> 34:16.023
There is both faith and fear, right?

34:16.083 --> 34:16.423
It's there.

34:17.344 --> 34:17.925
Coexist.

34:18.466 --> 34:21.389
It comes down to what you choose to trust in in that moment.

34:22.290 --> 34:26.475
And I've had plenty, plenty of times in my life where I trusted in the fear.

34:27.577 --> 34:31.982
And this let me down every stinking time, every time, right?

34:32.022 --> 34:39.571
There's not a single moment that I've trusted in the faith and allowed the faith to override the fear that I regret that decision or that moment.

34:39.792 --> 34:41.714
Now it hasn't always worked out the way I thought.

34:42.018 --> 34:45.441
but I've never regretted it, not one single time.

34:45.742 --> 34:48.044
So I don't know what situation you're facing.

34:48.104 --> 34:49.786
I don't know what crossroads you might be at.

34:49.846 --> 34:51.888
I don't know what's bringing up fear inside of you.

34:51.908 --> 34:57.994
It might have some do with your kids, might have to do with your marriage, might have to do with your job, career, where you're gonna live.

34:58.494 --> 35:03.439
There's so many things, right, that could bring up some kind of fear inside of you.

35:03.999 --> 35:08.744
I have no idea what it is, but what I do know is this, inside of you right now is both faith and fear.

35:09.765 --> 35:10.706
And you get to choose.

35:11.650 --> 35:13.852
Moses had that choice, right?

35:13.972 --> 35:28.367
And God used Moses in some really cool ways, but Moses constantly struggled with that tension between faith and fear, and many times in his life, he chose to identify with the fear, and every time he did that, it cost him, and it cost him greatly.

35:29.528 --> 35:40.018
And so if you're ever gonna step into this life that God has for you and become everything that you can possibly become, you've got in that moment of tension between fear and faith, say, I'm going to choose

35:40.418 --> 35:44.765
Even though it scares me to death, I'm going to step into this moment.

35:44.805 --> 35:45.826
I'm going to see what God does.

35:47.188 --> 35:54.600
Heavenly Father, we thank You so much for this day, for the opportunity to be here, to worship together, to hear Your Word.

35:54.660 --> 36:06.738
And God, I know, I know that in this moment there are hundreds of people in this room and watching online who are struggling with fear in some part of their life.

36:07.778 --> 36:12.423
And again, maybe it's a relationship thing or a finance thing or a vocational thing.

36:12.444 --> 36:13.284
I have no idea.

36:13.305 --> 36:20.373
But what I do know is that today God is trying to shift our minds.

36:21.935 --> 36:24.818
He's trying to change up the story that we've been telling ourselves.

36:24.838 --> 36:30.925
Because if we can change up the story, we've been telling ourselves everything in front of us will happen with so much more ease.

36:33.048 --> 36:34.930
And some people are stuck in the water fluke.

36:36.194 --> 36:38.617
And today, God, you're just trying to nudge them a little bit.

36:39.058 --> 36:44.244
You're trying to rewrite that story a little bit and move them from what if to what is.

36:46.086 --> 36:50.913
Because when we step into what is, oh, so many of those fears just kind of disappear.

36:52.214 --> 36:58.102
You're trying to drag them into what is, to try to point out to them what it is that is actually in their hand right now.

36:58.842 --> 37:04.850
What gifts, abilities, strengths, passions, intellect.

37:06.018 --> 37:11.924
gifts, abilities that they have right now and remind us that everything that we have is enough.

37:12.064 --> 37:14.887
It's sufficient for whatever it is you're calling us to do in our future.

37:16.789 --> 37:21.114
Some people are stuck in this loop of thinking that they're not enough and they're not qualified.

37:21.134 --> 37:32.946
And today you're just trying to shift them a little bit from being so focused on what they don't have to focus on what you do have and who you are.

37:34.210 --> 37:38.214
It's just reminded that we're never gonna be ready for the most difficult moments of our life.

37:38.895 --> 37:39.555
It's okay.

37:40.816 --> 37:45.741
Because every difficult moment we step into, we're not stepping into it alone, for you are with us.

37:47.663 --> 37:49.945
God, we are so thankful for you.

37:50.006 --> 37:57.072
We're thankful for your son, Jesus, who died on the cross, who resurrected three days later, defeating death for all of us.

37:58.914 --> 38:02.738
So if we choose to put our faith and our trust in you, we're forgiven of our sins.

38:06.626 --> 38:12.553
God, I pray today because I think there's a lot of us who have been set free, right?

38:12.653 --> 38:14.456
We've been forgiven of our sins.

38:14.496 --> 38:16.618
We've been set free from the penalty of death.

38:18.200 --> 38:21.524
But even though we've been set free, we still don't know what it looks like to live free.

38:24.047 --> 38:29.714
And I pray that today will be a step closer to learning what it means to live free, not just be set free.

38:31.874 --> 38:37.964
To live a life where we're dependent on you and what it is that you can do innocent through us because we don't want to be a slave to fear.

38:41.189 --> 38:44.293
We need to be reminded today of who we are in you.

38:45.696 --> 38:46.757
For it's in your name that we pray.

38:47.659 --> 38:52.306
Amen.

